A family in Keiyo North has asked well-wishers to help them raise Sh1.5 million help their daughter seek treatment in South Africa for a rare breast cancer.Joyce Kemunto, 18, was diagnosed with double breast cancer last year. Her parents Daniel Mutuku and Edna Moraa on Friday said they spent a lot of money taking her to herbalists for treatment before taking her to hospital.Moraa said after visits to Iten County Referral and Moi Teaching and Referral hospitals, Kemunto was referred to a hospital in South Africa.Mutuku, a casual worker, said a funds drive for the treatment, raised Sh20,000.Well-wishers can reach the family on and also send contributions to +254 708 080054.